on":"Wire reviewer output schemas (or adapters) into the real merge component and feed conflicting clause assessments; assert merged report contains both assessments, correct reviewer attribution, and no overwrite/drop.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.32,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Seam-map: multi-step orchestration seam (parallel agentic reviewers + collection + merge). MULTI-STEP applies directly: multiple real agentic steps in sequence/coordination. MOCK-HIDE: replacing reviewers with mocks can miss real timing/output-shape/agentic-result interactions that cause dropped findings. Rejection-gate: Agentic-only rejected because this is not one model judgment; it is end-to-end orchestration across three agentic stages plus merge.","test_description":"Execute the end-to-end pipeline on real contracts with real reviewer calls in parallel, then verify final unified report retains every finding from each reviewer (no loss/overwrite) and records merge outcomes for conflicts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.75}}]}
